Mapedit for X may be evaluated for 30 days. After that time, 
commercial and government users must pay for it (see below). 
Educational institutions and nonprofit organizations may
use the software without charge provided that a postcard
(or a note the letterhead of the organization) is sent
to the address at the end of this file. 

The Mapedit rate schedule is designed so that cost drops off quickly
after the first few copies are purchased. 

Copies 1-5: $25 per copy
Copies 6-20: $15 per copy
Copies 2l-100: $10 per copy
Unlimited site license, 10-mile radius: $1000

To take one example, 6 copies of Mapedit would cost $140:
the first 5 copies cost $25 apiece, and the sixth copy costs only $15.

To take another example, 50 copies of Mapedit would cost $650:
5 copies at $25 apiece, 15 copies at $15 apiece, and
30 copies at $10 apiece.

Note that on flat-fee site license orders I will provide 
registered-grade support to your technical support staff but 
cannot support individual end users.

